# Cadence environment configuration.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (preferred; git-ignored) or `.env` and fill in
# the values you need. Vite injects every variable prefixed with
# `VITE_` into the bundle at build time.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloud sync — Google Drive OAuth client ID
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Required only if you forked Cadence and want Drive sync to work in
# your build. Get one from the Google Cloud Console:
#
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create / pick a project, enable the Drive API.
#   3. APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen → External / Internal.
#   4. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth client ID.
#      - Type: Web application
#      - Authorized redirect URI: <your-pwa-origin>/?oauth=google
#   5. Paste the client ID below (looks like `…apps.googleusercontent.com`).
#
# See README → "Cloud sync (Google Drive…)" for the full walkthrough.
VITE_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
